result.execSummary:
The defendant Dakota Darrell Strebig was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Restitution Summary

Court calls case Nos. 16CF103, 16TR734 & 16CM61. Defendant Dakota Darrell Strebig in court with attorney Alec Phillip Nocco.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Agreement placed on the record by Atty Tlusty.  Victim rights complied. 16CF103 - DE entered a plea of no contest to Ct. 1 & 3.  16TR734 - DE entered a plea of no contest.  16CM61 - DE entered a plea of no contest to the charge.  Plea colloquy.  Factual basis exists.  Court found plea given freely, voluntarily and intelligently; accepted plea; found DE guilty.  Argument on jail sentence. 16CF103 - Court withheld sentence on Ct. 1 and placed DE on probation for 2 years with the following conditions: courts costs; DNA sample and surcharge; 30 days county jail with Huber; AODA; counseling as deemed appropriate by agent. Ct. 3 - Court withheld sentence and placed DE on probation for 2 years with the following conditions: court costs; DNA sample; AODA; counseling as deemed appropriate by agent.   Court dismissed, but read in Cts. 2 & 4. 16TR734 - Court imposed forfeiture of $845; $45 blood draw fee; 7 month driver's license revocation; AODA.  16CM61 - Court imposed court costs; DNA sample and surcharge; restitution of $206 plus surcharge; letter of apology to M.F., due within 30 days and pre-approved by Victim Witness Coordinator. ba
